# Sveltia CMS

Sveltia CMS is a Git-based, file-backed admin UI (successor to Netlify CMS / Decap CMS). Configuration is usually a public YAML file next to the admin `index.html`.

- Main docs: https://sveltiacms.app/en/docs/
- Configuration basics (formats, config URL, schema, security): https://sveltiacms.app/en/docs/config-basics
- AI-oriented full docs index: https://sveltiacms.app/llms.txt — detailed bundle: https://sveltiacms.app/llms-full.txt

## Project setup (this repo)

- Admin UI: `public/admin/index.html` (loads `@sveltia/cms` from unpkg)
- Config file: `public/admin/config.yml` (default location; no `<link rel="cms-config-url">` required unless you move or split config)
- Content folders (as in config): `/content/pages`, `/content/posts`
- Media: `/public/media` with `public_folder: /media` (adjust `repo` and paths when wiring GitHub)

## Configuration file

- Default: `config.yml` beside `index.html`, served e.g. at `/admin/config.yml`.
- **Public by design** — never put API keys, tokens, or passwords in the YAML.
- **YAML / TOML / JSON** supported; YAML is the usual choice for comments and readability. For TOML or JSON, add a `<link href="..." type="application/toml|application/json" rel="cms-config-url" />` in `<head>` per [Configuration Basics](https://sveltiacms.app/en/docs/config-basics).
- **Multiple files**: several `<link rel="cms-config-url">` tags merge in order; YAML anchors/aliases only work within a single file (merged objects are deep-merged).
- **Editor validation**: use the official JSON Schema at the top of `config.yml`:

```yaml
# yaml-language-server: $schema=https://unpkg.com/@sveltia/cms/schema/sveltia-cms.json
```

- **Runtime**: invalid config surfaces on the CMS login screen; prefer schema in the editor for complete feedback.

## Config layout (root structure)

Typical top-level keys (exact set depends on backends and media mode):

```yaml
backend:
  name: github # or gitlab, gitea, test — see Backends docs
  repo: org/repo
  branch: main # optional

# Option A — media committed in Git (classic Netlify-style)
media_folder: public/media
public_folder: /media

# Option B — Cloudflare R2 (browser uploads; see R2 section below)
# media_libraries: { ... }

collections: [] # entry collections and/or file collections

singletons: [] # optional; root-level list, NOT inside collections
```

Docs: [Collections overview](https://sveltiacms.app/en/docs/collections), [Media](https://sveltiacms.app/en/docs/media).

### Entry collection (folder of files)

Former Netlify/Decap “folder collection”: many entries, usually one file per entry under `folder`.

```yaml
collections:
  - name: posts
    label: Posts
    label_singular: Post
    folder: content/posts # repo-root-relative; leading / optional per docs examples
    create: true
    slug: "{{year}}-{{month}}-{{day}}-{{slug}}"
    extension: md # optional; default often md + YAML front matter
    fields:
      - { name: title, label: Title, widget: string }
      - { name: date, label: Date, widget: datetime }
      - { name: body, label: Body, widget: richtext }
```

- Required: `name`, `folder`, `fields`.
- Common: `label`, `label_singular`, `description`, `create`, `slug`, `extension`, `format`, nested `fields` / widgets.

Full options: [Entry collections](https://sveltiacms.app/en/docs/collections/entries).

### File collection (fixed files, no create/delete)

Group of predefined paths; editors change content, not the file list.

```yaml
collections:
  - name: pages
    label: Pages
    files:
      - name: about
        label: About page
        file: content/pages/about.md
        format: yaml-frontmatter # optional; often inferred from extension
        fields:
          - { name: title, label: Title, widget: string }
          - { name: body, label: Body, widget: richtext }
```

- Collection-level: `name`, `files` (array).
- Per file: `name`, `file`, `fields`; optional `label`, `format`.

Details: [File collections](https://sveltiacms.app/en/docs/collections/files).

### Singletons (one-off files at root)

Declared as a **root** `singletons` array (not nested under `collections`). One logical document per `file` path.

```yaml
singletons:
  - name: settings
    label: Site settings
    file: content/settings.yaml
    fields:
      - { name: site_title, label: Site title, widget: string }
      - { name: tagline, label: Tagline, widget: text }
```

Details: [Singletons](https://sveltiacms.app/en/docs/collections/singletons).

### Cloudflare R2 (media library)

S3-compatible uploads from the browser; configure under `media_libraries.cloudflare_r2`. **Do not** put the Secret Access Key in YAML — users enter it in the CMS UI (stored in browser); only `access_key_id` and non-secret bucket/account/public URL belong in config.

```yaml
media_libraries:
  cloudflare_r2:
    access_key_id: "<64-char R2 token id>"
    bucket: my-r2-bucket
    account_id: "<cloudflare account id>"
    public_url: https://pub-xxxx.r2.dev # or https://media.example.com
    prefix: cms-uploads/ # optional key prefix in bucket
    jurisdiction: default # optional: default | eu | fedramp
```

- `public_url` is required for previews (R2 S3 API is always authenticated).
- R2 bucket **CORS** must allow your CMS origin with `GET`, `PUT`, `HEAD` and the Sig v4 headers the app sends.
- If the site uses **CSP**, allow the R2 API host and `public_url` host per [Cloudflare R2](https://sveltiacms.app/en/docs/media/cloudflare-r2) and [Security / CSP](https://sveltiacms.app/en/docs/security#setting-up-content-security-policy).

Full guide: [Cloudflare R2](https://sveltiacms.app/en/docs/media/cloudflare-r2).

## Concepts (map to docs)

| Topic | Docs area |
|-------|-----------|
| Backend (GitHub, GitLab, Gitea, test) | https://sveltiacms.app/en/docs/ — Backends |
| Media storage (internal, S3, R2, …) | [Media](https://sveltiacms.app/en/docs/media), [R2](https://sveltiacms.app/en/docs/media/cloudflare-r2) |
| Entry collections (`folder`) | [Entry collections](https://sveltiacms.app/en/docs/collections/entries) |
| File collections (`files`) | [File collections](https://sveltiacms.app/en/docs/collections/files) |
| Singletons (root `singletons`) | [Singletons](https://sveltiacms.app/en/docs/collections/singletons) |
| Field widgets (`string`, `markdown`, `image`, `relation`, …) | [Fields](https://sveltiacms.app/en/docs/fields) |

Netlify/Decap-style keys (`backend`, `media_folder`, `public_folder`, `collections`, `folder`, `fields`, `widget`) remain familiar; confirm behavior and new options in the Sveltia docs for each feature.

## Nuxt / content repo notes

- Paths in `config.yml` should match how the CMS and your framework resolve files in the repo (this project uses `/content/...` and `/public/media` in `config.yml`); keep `folder` / `media_folder` aligned with Nuxt Content and static asset paths.
- After changing collections or front matter shape, keep Nuxt Content (`content.config.ts`, queries, page types) in sync with the CMS schema.

## Customization

Preview styles/templates, custom components, manual JS/TS init, and event hooks are documented under **Customizing Sveltia CMS** on the same doc site.
